                <head>417. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On April 15, the Department of State transmitted to the White House a memorandum
                    asking the President to send personal messages to Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_NJ3">Nehru</persName>, the Shah of Iran, the <persName
                        corresp="#p_HIT1">King</persName> of Morocco, Emperor Haile Selassie, and
                    President Bourguiba of Tunisia requesting support for the U.S.-Canadian proposal
                    at the Law of the Sea Conference. The same memorandum noted that Secretary of
                    State Herter was sending similar messages to 20 Prime Ministers or Foreign
                    Ministers. (Department of State, Central Files, 399.731/4–1560)</p>
                <pb facs="0823" n="793" xml:id="pg_793"/>
                <p>The texts of the 5 Presidential messages and the 20 sent by Herter were
                    transmitted telegraphically to the appropriate posts on April 15 and 16. (<hi
                        rend="italic">Ibid</hi>., 399.731/4–15.60 and 4–1660)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
